@startuml
title Host transition: Isolated -> Browser -> Isolated

actor User
participant "OnboardingActivity\n(host observer)" as OA
participant "LinearOnboardingOrchestrator\n@AppScope" as Orch
participant "BrowserActivity\n(host observer)" as BA

User -> OA : taps primary on last\nIsolatedContext step
OA -> Orch : onEvent(PrimaryClicked)
Orch -> Orch : transition -> Advance\ncurrentStep = first BrowserContext step
Orch --> OA : state emits InProgress(<browser step>)
OA -> OA : expectedHost = BrowserContext\nstartActivity(BrowserActivity)\nfinish()

User -> BA : (now foreground)
BA -> Orch : observe state
Orch --> BA : InProgress(<browser step>)
BA -> BA : expectedHost = BrowserContext (matches)\nrender browser-context step

User -> BA : completes browser-context step
BA -> Orch : onEvent(...)
Orch -> Orch : transition -> Advance\ncurrentStep = next IsolatedContext step
Orch --> BA : state emits InProgress(<isolated step>)
BA -> BA : expectedHost = IsolatedContext\nstartActivity(OnboardingActivity)\nfinish()

note over OA, BA
  hostTransitionInitiated guard prevents double-firing
  within a single activity instance.
  state-derived: activity recreation re-evaluates
  expectedHost from current state.
end note
@enduml
